paragraphs.title: Get Live Ratings from Cassandra
paragraphs.text:
val cassandraConfig = Map("keyspace" -> "advancedspark", "table" -> "item_ratings")

val itemRatingsDF = sqlContext.read.format("org.apache.spark.sql.cassandra")
  .options(cassandraConfig)
  .load()
  .select($"userid", $"itemid", $"rating", $"timestamp")
  .withColumnRenamed("userid", "userId")
  .withColumnRenamed("itemid", "itemId")
  .as("itemRatings")
  
z.show(itemRatingsDF.sort($"userId" asc))

paragraphs.title: Train ALS Model With the training dataset
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.recommendation.ALS

val rank = 5 // this is k, number of latent factors we think exist
val maxIterations = 10
val convergenceThreshold = 0.01
val implicitPrefs = false
val alpha = 1.0
val nonnegative = true

val als = new ALS()
  .setRank(rank)
  .setMaxIter(maxIterations)
  .setRegParam(convergenceThreshold)
  .setImplicitPrefs(implicitPrefs)
  .setAlpha(alpha)
  .setNonnegative(nonnegative)
  .setUserCol("userId")
  .setItemCol("itemId")
  .setRatingCol("rating")
  .setPredictionCol("prediction")

paragraphs.title: Setup ML Pipeline
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.Pipeline

val pipeline = new Pipeline()
  .setStages(Array(als))

paragraphs.title: Setup Model Evaluator
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.evaluation.RegressionEvaluator

val modelEvaluator = new RegressionEvaluator()
  .setMetricName("rmse")
  .setLabelCol("rating")
  .setPredictionCol("prediction")

paragraphs.title: Build Param Grid Search
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.ParamGridBuilder

val paramGrid = new ParamGridBuilder()
  .addGrid(als.rank, Array(5, 10, 15))
  .addGrid(als.maxIter, Array(10, 20))
  .addGrid(als.regParam, Array(.01, .001))
  .build()
  
paramGrid.size

paragraphs.title: Setup Cross Validator
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.CrossValidator

val numFolds = 2

val modelValidator = new CrossValidator()
  .setEstimator(pipeline)
  .setEvaluator(modelEvaluator)
  .setEstimatorParamMaps(paramGrid)
  .setNumFolds(numFolds)

paragraphs.title: Train CrossValidator Model To Find Best Model
paragraphs.text: val crossValidatorModel = modelValidator.fit(itemRatingsDF)

paragraphs.title: Find Best Param Grid Options
paragraphs.text:
val avgMetricsParamGrid = crossValidatorModel.avgMetrics

val combined = paramGrid.zip(avgMetricsParamGrid)
  .sortBy(paramGridMetricTuple => (1 - paramGridMetricTuple._2))
  .take(1)(0)._1

paragraphs.title: Find Best Pipeline Model

import org.apache.spark.ml.PipelineModel

val bestPipelineModel = crossValidatorModel.bestModel.asInstanceOf[PipelineModel]

paragraphs.title: Extract Best Recomendation Model
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.recommendation.ALSModel

val bestRecommendationModel = bestPipelineModel.stages(0).asInstanceOf[ALSModel]

paragraphs.title: Find all (User, item) pairs without an existing Rating
paragraphs.text:
val allDistinctUsersDF = itemRatingsDF.select($"userId").dropDuplicates()

val allDistinctUserItemPairsDF = allDistinctUsersDF
  .join(itemsDF.select($"itemId"))
  .select($"userId", $"itemId")
  .distinct()
  .coalesce(1)

z.show(allDistinctUserItemPairsDF.sort($"userId", $"itemId"))

paragraphs.title: Generate Recommendations for (user, Item) Pairs without existing ratings
paragraphs.text:
val recommendationsDF = bestRecommendationModel.transform(allDistinctUserItemPairsDF)
  .as("recommendations")
  .cache()
  
z.show(recommendationsDF.sort($"userId", $"itemId"))

result.msg: recommendationsDF: org.apache.spark.sql.DataFrame = [userId: int, itemId: bigint, prediction: float]

paragraphs.title: Enrich the Recommendations
paragraphs.text:
val enrichedRecommendationsDF = 
   recommendationsDF.join(itemsDF, $"items.itemId" === $"recommendations.itemId")
   .select($"userId", $"items.itemId", $"title", $"tags", $"prediction", $"img")
   .sort($"userId", $"prediction" desc, $"items.itemId")
   .na.drop(Seq("prediction"))
   
z.show(enrichedRecommendationsDF.select($"userId", $"itemId", $"title", $"prediction"))

paragraphs.title: Store Recommendations in ElasticSearch
paragraphs.text:
import org.elasticsearch.spark.sql._

val esConfig = Map("pushdown" -> "true", "es.nodes" -> "127.0.0.1", "es.port" -> "9200")

enrichedRecommendationsDF.write.format("org.elasticsearch.spark.sql")
  .mode("overwrite")
  .options(esConfig)
  .save("advancedspark/personalized-als")

z.show(enrichedRecommendationsDF)

paragraphs.title: Calculate Predicted Rating for a Given userId and ItemId - compare Prediction to above
paragraphs.text:
import com.advancedspark.ml.BLAS
import com.advancedspark.ml.Vectors

// User 21619
val givenUserId = 21619
val givenUserFactors = userFactorsDF.select($"userId", $"userFactors")
  .where($"userId" === givenUserId)
  .map(row => row.getSeq[Double](1).toArray)
  .collect()(0)

// Item 10006 - Tom Cruise
val givenItemId = 10006
val givenItemFactors = itemFactorsDF.select($"itemId", $"itemFactors")
  .where($"itemId" === givenItemId)
  .map(row => row.getSeq[Double](1).toArray)
  .collect()(0)
  
val givenUserFactorsVector = Vectors.dense(givenUserFactors)
val givenItemFactorsVector = Vectors.dense(givenItemFactors)

// Take dot product of the User x Item vectors
// This should equal the prediction value in the offline-generated matrix
val prediction = BLAS.dot(givenUserFactorsVector, givenItemFactorsVector)
